the%20aging%20T-55%2C%20to%20Russia's%20defense%20ministry.%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20via%20Getty%20Images%20and%20Jack%20Esten%2FPicture%20Post%2FHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20biggest%20film%20studio%20said%20it%20helped%20shore%20up%20the%20Kremlin's%20losses%20in%202023%20with%2036%20aging%20tanks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMosfilm's%20head%20told%20Putin%20that%20it%20donated%2028%20T-55%20tanks%20and%20eight%20PT-76%20tanks%20to%20the%20defense%20ministry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussian%20troops%20have%20used%20similar%2C%20aging%20tanks%20as%20fire%20support%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Russia%20hunts%20for%20more%20war%20gear%2C%20its%20biggest%20film%20studio%20has%20stepped%20up%20%E2%80%94%20with%20movie%20props.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20director%20general%20of%20Mosfilm%2C%20Karen%20Shakhnazarov%2C%20met%20with%20Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20discuss%20the%20studio's%20profits%20and%20film%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20spoke%20mainly%20on%20their%20aspirations%20for%20the%20company%2C%20with%20Shakhnazarov%20boasting%20that%20Mosfilm%20was%20on%20par%20in%20scale%20with%20Hollywood%20firms%20like%20Warner%20Bros.%20and%20Universal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20Shakhnazarov%20ended%20the%20conversation%20on%20a%20note%20about%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Shakhnazarov%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fen.kremlin.ru%2Fevents%2Fpresident%2Fnews%2F75562%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20transcript%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20the%20Kremlin.%20%26quot%3BIn%202023%2C%20we%20handed%20over%2028%20T-55%20tanks%2C%20eight%20PT-76%20tanks%2C%20six%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%2C%20and%20eight%20trucks%20we%20had%20in%20our%20military%20department%20to%20the%20Armed%20Forces.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20knew%20that%20they%20needed%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Shakhnazarov%20added%2C%20saying%20Russia's%20defense%20ministry%20took%20the%20vehicles%20into%20its%20inventory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMosfilm%20is%20our%20pride%2C%26quot%3B%20Putin%20responded%2C%20per%20the%20transcript.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mosfilm's%20director%20general%20sits%20at%20a%20table%20with%20Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20to%20discuss%20the%20studio's%20profits.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6736d5bdede4eeae3927c016%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22580%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20head%20of%20Mosfilm%2C%20Shakhnazarov%2C%20met%20with%20Putin%20on%20Wednesday.%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20immediately%20clear%20whether%20any%20of%20Mosfilm's%20tanks%20saw%20action%20in%20Ukraine%20or%20whether%20they%20were%20even%20in%20the%20right%20condition%20to%20be%20usable%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mosfilm.ru%2Fservices%2Fmilitary%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMosfilm's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20the%20studio%20has%20over%20190%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20armored%20personnel%20carriers%2C%20and%20self-propelled%20guns%2C%20though%20it%20described%20them%20as%20being%20%26quot%3Bdisguised%26quot%3B%20as%20equipment%20from%20various%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20equipment%20is%20props%20(stage%20production%20equipment)%2C%20is%20in%20good%20working%20order%2C%20and%20is%20ready%20for%20filming%20several%20movies%20simultaneously%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20website%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20Soviet-era%20tanks%20mentioned%20by%20Shakhnazarov%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-shows-russia-tank-topped-with-ridiculously-tall-cage-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20medium%20tank%20T-55%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20light%20tank%20PT-76%20%E2%80%94%20were%20produced%20in%20the%201940s%20and%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20T-55%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20produced%20tanks%20in%20the%20world%2C%20was%20a%20hallmark%20of%20the%20early%20Cold%20War.%20It's%20so%20old%20that%20it's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ussalabama.com%2Fexplore%2Ftanks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20featured%20in%20museums%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20militaries%20around%20the%20world%20still%20use%20these%20tanks.%20But%20they're%20two%20generations%20behind%20the%20modern%20arms%20being%20used%20today%2C%20and%20have%20been%20largely%20considered%20obsolete%20in%20Russia's%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Shakhnazarov's%20statement%20comes%20as%20Moscow%20has%20struggled%20to%20maintain%20its%20inventory%20of%20armored%20vehicles%20amid%20heavy%20losses%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFigures%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oryxspioenkop.com%2F2022%2F02%2Fattack-on-europe-documenting-equipment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDutch%20open-source%20tracking%20group%20Oryx%3C%2Fa%3E%20say%20that%20Russia%20has%20lost%2010%2C888%20armored%20vehicles%20since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20including%203%2C558%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow%20has%20been%20driving%20up%20production%20to%20fill%20the%20gap%2C%20dumping%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-crisis-ukraine-war-moscow-inflation-sanctions-putin-spending-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%206%25%20of%20its%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20defense%20spending%20on%20guns%2C%20ammunition%2C%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strain%20on%20its%20forces%20began%20showing%20more%20clearly%20in%202023%2C%20as%20open-source%20intelligence%20groups%20noticed%20tanks%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-taken-tanks-from-1940s-out-of-storage-monitoring-group-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1940s%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%